 &intro;

 <part id="tutorial">
<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=bb02779b8684865194f4bb1a33a43fa1 sig_cn_org=bb02779b8684865194f4bb1a33a43fa1 source=14.1 
  <title>Tutorial</title>
________________________________________________________-->
  <title>教程</title>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=bb02779b8684865194f4bb1a33a43fa1 -->

  <partintro>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=8f460c04c426c697e30f52eb4a6d7aa5 sig_cn_org=d19500fb4204e49bff62c6b6792a6abf source=17.4 
   <para>
    Welcome to the <productname>PostgreSQL</productname> Tutorial.  The
    tutorial is intended to give an introduction
    to <productname>PostgreSQL</productname>, relational database
    concepts, and the SQL language. We assume some general knowledge about
    how to use computers and no particular Unix or programming experience is
    required.  This tutorial is intended to provide hands-on experience with
    important aspects of the <productname>PostgreSQL</productname> system.
    It makes no attempt to be a comprehensive treatment of the topics it covers.
   </para>
________________________________________________________-->
   <para>
    欢迎使用<productname>PostgreSQL</productname>教程。本教程旨在介绍
    <productname>PostgreSQL</productname>、关系数据库概念以及SQL语言。我们假设
    读者具备一定的计算机使用基础，但不要求具备特定的Unix或编程经验。
    本教程旨在提供<productname>PostgreSQL</productname>系统重要方面的实践经验，
    并不试图对所涉及的主题进行全面讲解。
   </para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=8f460c04c426c697e30f52eb4a6d7aa5 -->

<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=4325f3aa2a415e3de80216a31d2fbd8b sig_cn_org=2670e0d1fa401b51efa33c19f4032ab6 source=17.4 
   <para>
    After you have successfully completed this tutorial you will want to
    read the <xref linkend="sql"/> section to gain a better understanding
    of the SQL language, or <xref linkend="client-interfaces"/> for
    information about developing applications with
    <productname>PostgreSQL</productname>.  Those who provision and
    manage their own PostgreSQL installation should also read <xref linkend="admin"/>.
   </para>
________________________________________________________-->
   <para>
    完成本教程后，您可能想阅读<xref linkend="sql"/>部分，以更好地理解
    SQL语言，或<xref linkend="client-interfaces"/>，了解如何使用
    <productname>PostgreSQL</productname>开发应用程序。那些自行配置和
    管理PostgreSQL安装的用户也应阅读<xref linkend="admin"/>。
   </para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=4325f3aa2a415e3de80216a31d2fbd8b -->
  </partintro>

  &start;
  &query;
  &advanced;

 </part>

 <part id="sql">
<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=5e4ccd77b20c99d758068a3593a92373 sig_cn_org=5e4ccd77b20c99d758068a3593a92373 source=14.1 
  <title>The SQL Language</title>
________________________________________________________-->
  <title>SQL 语言</title>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=5e4ccd77b20c99d758068a3593a92373 -->

  <partintro>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=647c9580e8d19f7a404aacf74d2e120c sig_cn_org=9af652ebd6c20f149121d307d05ebb36 source=17.4 
   <para>
    This part describes the use of the <acronym>SQL</acronym> language
    in <productname>PostgreSQL</productname>.  We start with
    describing the general syntax of <acronym>SQL</acronym>, then
    how to create tables, how to populate the database, and how to
    query it.  The middle part lists the available data types and
    functions for use in <acronym>SQL</acronym> commands.  Lastly,
    we address several aspects of importance for tuning a database.
   </para>
________________________________________________________-->
   <para>
    本部分描述了在<acronym>SQL</acronym>语言在<productname>PostgreSQL</productname>中的使用。
    我们首先介绍<acronym>SQL</acronym>的一般语法，然后介绍如何创建表、如何填充数据库以及如何查询。
    中间部分列出了可用于<acronym>SQL</acronym>命令的数据类型和函数。最后，我们讨论了调优数据库
    的几个重要方面。
   </para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=647c9580e8d19f7a404aacf74d2e120c -->

<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=2a2e43b3b356310ccf0829feeb43deb4 sig_cn_org=f9b45b38f959e9a10826255b476a3e09 source=17.4 
   <para>
    The information is arranged so that a novice user can
    follow it from start to end and gain a full understanding of the topics
    without having to refer forward too many times.  The chapters are
    intended to be self-contained, so that advanced users can read the
    chapters individually as they choose.  The information is presented
    in narrative form with topical units. Readers looking for a complete
    description of a particular command are encouraged to review
    the <xref linkend="reference"/>.
   </para>
________________________________________________________-->
   <para>
    信息的安排使得初学者可以从头到尾跟随，充分理解各个主题，
    无需频繁向后查阅。各章节设计为独立完整，方便高级用户根据
    需要单独阅读。信息以叙述形式和专题单元呈现。希望获得某个
    特定命令完整描述的读者，建议查阅<xref linkend="reference"/>。
   </para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=2a2e43b3b356310ccf0829feeb43deb4 -->

<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=137cb78d41de7ccc566b2f6b8ebae2ec sig_cn_org=d76c619fd1b0123995f6656ef1abf134 source=17.4 
   <para>
    Readers should know how to connect to a
    <productname>PostgreSQL</productname> database and issue
    <acronym>SQL</acronym> commands.  Readers that are unfamiliar with
    these issues are encouraged to read <xref linkend="tutorial"/>
    first.  <acronym>SQL</acronym> commands are typically entered
    using the <productname>PostgreSQL</productname> interactive terminal
    <application>psql</application>, but other programs that have
    similar functionality can be used as well.
   </para>
________________________________________________________-->
   <para>
    读者应了解如何连接到
    <productname>PostgreSQL</productname>数据库并发出
    <acronym>SQL</acronym>命令。对于不熟悉这些问题的读者，建议先阅读
    <xref linkend="tutorial"/>。<acronym>SQL</acronym>命令通常使用
    <productname>PostgreSQL</productname>交互式终端
    <application>psql</application>输入，但也可以使用具有类似功能的其他程序。
   </para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=137cb78d41de7ccc566b2f6b8ebae2ec -->
  </partintro>

  &syntax;
  &ddl;
  &dml;
  &queries;
  &datatype;
  &func;
  &typeconv;
  &indices;
  &textsearch;
  &mvcc;
  &perform;
  &parallel;

 </part>

 <part id="admin">
<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=3a620f89a1d67d59c661e2024d5affdb sig_cn_org=3a620f89a1d67d59c661e2024d5affdb source=14.1 
  <title>Server Administration</title>
________________________________________________________-->
  <title>服务器管理</title>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=3a620f89a1d67d59c661e2024d5affdb -->

  <partintro>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=e0d5ca5bf744610517031569cc5d14f8 sig_cn_org=fa0eb68b2d6ca61f84a64113d82b8bf0 source=17.4 
   <para>
    This part covers topics that are of interest to a
    <productname>PostgreSQL</productname> administrator.  This includes
    installation, configuration of the server, management of users
    and databases, and maintenance tasks. Anyone running
    <productname>PostgreSQL</productname> server, even for
    personal use, but especially in production, should be familiar
    with these topics.
   </para>
________________________________________________________-->
   <para>
    本部分涵盖了<productname>PostgreSQL</productname>管理员感兴趣的主题。包括安装、
    服务器配置、用户和数据库管理以及维护任务。任何运行<productname>PostgreSQL</productname>
    服务器的人，即使是个人使用，尤其是在生产环境中，都应熟悉这些主题。
   </para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=e0d5ca5bf744610517031569cc5d14f8 -->

<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=a4c6c80bce018150c71328467d4931dc sig_cn_org=820ec7e4907931be61a43dffc8dac23d source=17.4 
   <para>
    The information attempts to be in the order in which
    a new user should read it.  The chapters are self-contained and
    can be read individually as desired.  The information is presented
    in a narrative form in topical units.  Readers looking for a complete
    description of a command are encouraged to review the
    <xref linkend="reference"/>.
   </para>
________________________________________________________-->
   <para>
    信息尝试按照新用户应阅读的顺序排列。各章节内容独立，
    可根据需要单独阅读。信息以专题单元的叙述形式呈现。
    寻求命令完整描述的读者建议查阅
    <xref linkend="reference"/>.
   </para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=a4c6c80bce018150c71328467d4931dc -->

<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=46b5e0ee62ea4eddb0b17a42dbd03a99 sig_cn_org=8436504c0e185fa2cd6a0648dc99d5f5 source=17.4 
   <para>
    The first few chapters are written so they can be understood
    without prerequisite knowledge, so new users who need to set
    up their own server can begin their exploration. The rest of this
    part is about tuning and management; that material
    assumes that the reader is familiar with the general use of
    the <productname>PostgreSQL</productname> database system.  Readers are
    encouraged review the <xref linkend="tutorial"/> and <xref
    linkend="sql"/> parts for additional information.
   </para>
________________________________________________________-->
   <para>
    前几章的内容编写得易于理解，无需先验知识，因此需要搭建自己服务器的新用户
    可以开始探索。本部分的其余内容涉及调优和管理；这些内容假设读者熟悉
    <productname>PostgreSQL</productname>数据库系统的一般使用。建议读者查阅
    <xref linkend="tutorial"/>和<xref linkend="sql"/>部分以获取更多信息。
   </para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=46b5e0ee62ea4eddb0b17a42dbd03a99 -->
  </partintro>

  &installbin;
  &installation;
  &runtime;
  &config;
  &client-auth;
  &user-manag;
  &manage-ag;
  &charset;
  &maintenance;
  &backup;
  &high-availability;
  &monitoring;
  &wal;
  &logical-replication;
  &jit;
  &regress;

 </part>

 <part id="client-interfaces">
<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=3d92464749d1878f65ae1742df32ca00 sig_cn_org=3d92464749d1878f65ae1742df32ca00 source=14.1 
  <title>Client Interfaces</title>
________________________________________________________-->
  <title>客户端接口</title>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=3d92464749d1878f65ae1742df32ca00 -->

  <partintro>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=24e60e731d99df52793f3ccf79f04d2a sig_cn_org=4798953f7fdaedee06a3aa58f6079975 source=17.4 
   <para>
    This part describes the client programming interfaces distributed
    with <productname>PostgreSQL</productname>.  Each of these chapters can be
    read independently.  There are many external programming
    interfaces for client programs that are distributed separately. They
    contain their own documentation (<xref linkend="external-projects"/>
    lists some of the more popular ones).  Readers of this part should be
    familiar with using <acronym>SQL</acronym> to manipulate
    and query the database (see <xref linkend="sql"/>) and of course
    with the programming language of their choice.
   </para>
________________________________________________________-->
   <para>
    本部分介绍随<productname>PostgreSQL</productname>分发的客户端编程接口。每章内容均可独立阅读。
    有许多单独分发的外部客户端编程接口。它们包含自己的文档（<xref linkend="external-projects"/>
    列出了一些较受欢迎的接口）。本部分的读者应熟悉使用<acronym>SQL</acronym>操作和查询数据库（参见
    <xref linkend="sql"/>），当然还应熟悉所选的编程语言。
   </para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=24e60e731d99df52793f3ccf79f04d2a -->
  </partintro>

  &libpq;
  &lobj;
  &ecpg;
  &infoschema;

 </part>

 <part id="server-programming">
<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=80affb8fda1273fd2ba34f39fe3ad3e2 sig_cn_org=80affb8fda1273fd2ba34f39fe3ad3e2 source=14.1 
  <title>Server Programming</title>
________________________________________________________-->
  <title>服务器编程</title>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=80affb8fda1273fd2ba34f39fe3ad3e2 -->

  <partintro>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=705a484464052d5bc66b0bfb198fbb57 sig_cn_org=391650e392afc3b6776c96cdd338b136 source=17.4 
   <para>
    This part is about extending the server functionality with
    user-defined functions, data types, triggers, etc.  These are
    advanced topics which should be approached only after all
    the other user documentation about <productname>PostgreSQL</productname> has
    been understood.  Later chapters in this part describe the server-side
    programming languages available in the
    <productname>PostgreSQL</productname> distribution as well as
    general issues concerning server-side programming.  It
    is essential to read at least the earlier sections of <xref
    linkend="extend"/> (covering functions) before diving into the
    material about server-side programming.
   </para>
________________________________________________________-->
   <para>
    本部分介绍如何通过用户定义的函数、数据类型、触发器等扩展服务器功能。
    这些是高级主题，只有在理解了关于<productname>PostgreSQL</productname>的所有其他用户文档后
    才应进行学习。本部分后面的章节描述了<productname>PostgreSQL</productname>发行版中
    可用的服务器端编程语言以及有关服务器端编程的一般问题。阅读至少<xref
    linkend="extend"/>的早期章节（涵盖函数）对于深入了解服务器端编程内容是必不可少的。
   </para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=705a484464052d5bc66b0bfb198fbb57 -->
  </partintro>

  &extend;
  &trigger;
  &event-trigger;
  &rules;

  &xplang;
  &plsql;
  &pltcl;
  &plperl;
  &plpython;

  &spi;
  &bgworker;
  &logicaldecoding;
  &replication-origins;
  &archive-modules;

 </part>

